s|TAG_BIOGRAPHY_1|<b>Steve Jobs</b> was born on February 24, 1955 in San Francisco, California, U.S.A. He is the co-founder, Chairman and CEO of Apple Inc. He also was the CEO of Pixar Animation Studios until it was acquired by the Walt Disney Company. He currently sits on the Board of Directors of Walt Disney Company's and is largest individual shareholder of the company. Under his guindenc, Apple has created the Macintosh, the iPod, the iTunes Store, and the iPhone, among other things. |g
